VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT xpath\.evaluate\s*\(|XPathExpression\.evaluate\s*\(|XPath\.compile\s*\(
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:request|getParameter|input|query|\+ && MISSING:XPathVariableResolver|parameterized|encodeForXPath
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects XPath evaluation calls that may use user-supplied input in the expression.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for XPath Injection: XPathExpression with Concatenation.
